.START 

Kaydon Corp. named Lawrence J. Cawley chairman, succeeding Richard A. Shantz, who is retiring. 

Mr. Cawley, 55 years old, has been president and chief executive officer since 1987.
He will retain the chief executive position, but relinquish the president's job to Stephen K. Clough, who was named president and chief operating officer.
Mr. Clough, 36, had been vice president and general manager of Kaydon's bearing division.
Mr. Clough also was appointed a director of the maker of auto engine parts. 

Mr. Shantz, 53, joined Kaydon in 1971 as president.
He was chief executive in 1984, when the company went public.
Mr. Shantz will remain a director of the company. 

